data.def: "A form of loss of vision caused by damage to the visual cortex rather than a defect in the eye." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of the glial cells
data.def: "An abnormality of the glia cell." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Glia are nonneuronal cells of the nervous system that provide physical support, respond to injury, regulate the composition of the extracellular milieu, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

data.name: Abnormality of the astrocytes
data.def: "An abnormality of astrocytes." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Astrocytes represent a class of large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system.

data.name: Impulsivity
data.def: "An abnormality of the microglial cells. They are also known as brain-resident macrophages or hortega cells." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Microglial cells represent a central nervous system macrophage found in the parenchyma of the central nervous system.

data.name: Abnormality of the thoracic spine
data.def: "An abnormality of the thoracic vertebral column." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of the lumbar spine
data.def: "An abnormality of the lumbar vertebral column." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Self-injurious behavior
data.def: "Aggression towards oneself." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Hypoplasia of the ear cartilage
data.def: "A sectoral indentation of the crystalline lens, usually due to zonular weakness or absence." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Hypercoagulability
data.def: "An abnormality of coagulation associated with an increased risk of thrombosis." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Lichenification
data.def: "Thickening and hardening of the epidermis seen with exaggeration of normal skin lines." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Bronchogenic cyst
data.def: "A rare congenital cystic lesion of the lungs in the mediastinum." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Pancreatic fibrosis
data.def: "A horizontal cleft of the face, varying from slight widening of the mouth, to a cleft extending to the ear." [DDD:jhurst]
data.comment: Usually, these clefts are unilateral and do not extend beyond the anterior border of the masseter. Transverse clefts are thought to develop either due to failure of the maxillary and mandibular processes to fuse or a disruption in the processes after fusing.

data.name: Hypertensive crisis
data.def: "An anomaly of one or more epiphyses of one or more vertebrae." []

data.name: Abnormality of the soft palate
data.def: "An abnormality of the soft palate." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormal eating behavior
data.def: "Abnormal eating habit with excessive or insufficient consumption of food or any other abnormal pattern of food consumption." []
data.comment: Note that this HPO term refers to an abnormal eating habit but does not directly refer to an eating disorder, which is a psychological disorder that is characterized by one or more abnormal eating behaviors.

data.name: Vascular neoplasm
data.def: "A benign or malignant neoplasm (tumour) originating in the vascular system." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Chest pain
data.def: "An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) localized to the chest." []

data.name: Atelectasis
data.def: "Collapse of part of a lung associated with absence of inflation (air) of that part." [HPPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of salivation
data.def: "A state of abnormally elevated or irritable mood, arousal, and or energy levels." [PMID:15104084]
data.comment: Positive symptoms, such as delusions and hallucinations (especially of voices), are common, and any Schneiderian first-rank symptoms are particularly indicative of the illness. Negative symptoms include social withdrawal, impairment of ego boundaries, and loss of energy and initiative. Schizophrenia is diagnosed only if symptoms persist for at least one month. The illness can spontaneously remit, run a course with infrequent or frequent relapses, or become chronic. The prognosis has improved with antipsychotic drugs and with vigorous psychological and social management and rehabilitation. The many causes include genetic factors, environmental stress, and various triggering factors.

data.name: Gangrene
data.def: "A serious and potentially life-threatening condition that arises when a considerable mass of body tissue dies (necrosis)." [ISBN:9780781770873]
data.comment: This may occur after an injury or infection, or in people suffering from any chronic health problem affecting blood circulation. The prime cause of gangrene is reduced blood supply to the affected tissues, which results in cell death. Diabetes and long-term smoking increase the risk of suffering from gangrene. There are different types of gangrene with different symptoms, such as dry gangrene, wet gangrene, gas gangrene, internal gangrene and necrotising fasciitis. Treatment options include debridement (or, in severe cases, amputation) of the affected body parts, antibiotics, vascular surgery, maggot therapy or hyperbaric oxygen therapy.

data.name: Abnormality of the lymphatic system
data.def: "An anomaly of the lymphatic system, a network of lymphatic vessels that carry a clear fluid called lymph unidirectionally towards either the right lymphatic duct or the thoracic duct, which in turn drain into the right and left subclavian veins respectively." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of the placenta
data.def: "An abnormality of the placenta, the organ that connects the developing fetus to the uterine wall to enable nutrient uptake, waste elimination, and gas exchange." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Hyperostosis
data.def: "Excessive growth or abnormal thickening of bone tissue." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Hyperostosis refers to a localized bone overgrowth process (as opposed to sclerosis, which refers to a generalized disturbance with increased bone density).

data.name: Exostoses
data.def: "An exostosis is a benign growth the projects outward from the bone surface. It is cappped by cartilage, and arises from a bone that develops from cartilage." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Dural ectasia is one of the major manifestations of Marfan syndrome. It may cause low back pain, headaches and neurological signs such as weakness and loss of bowel and bladder function, but in many patients it is asymptomatic. It is also a cause of posterior vertebral scalloping present in radiographs in patients who are diagnosed with Neurofibromatosis. Dural ectasia may also manifest in Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome, cauda equina syndrome and in ankylosing spondylitis.

data.name: Breast aplasia
data.def: "Failure to develop and congenital absence of the breast." []

data.name: Hernia
data.def: "A bony protrusion present on the midline of the hard palate." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Aplasia/Hypoplasia of the pancreas
data.def: "A congential underdevelopment (aplasia or hypoplasia) of the pancreas." [HPO:sdoelken]
data.comment: If possible, a more precise term should be chosen for annotation.

data.name: Abnormality of the periungual region
data.def: "An abnormality of the region around the nails of the fingers or toes." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Sepsis
data.def: "Systemic inflammatory response to infection." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Ungual fibromas are characteristic of tuberous sclerosis.

data.name: Intestinal fistula
data.def: "An abnormal connection between the gut and another hollow organ, such as the bladder, urethra, vagina, or other regions of the gastrointestinal tract." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Renal artery stenosis can lead to hypertension and chronic kidney disease (due to chronic renal ischemia). The hypertension is caused by activation of the renin-angiotensin-aldosterone system.

data.name: Glomerulopathy
data.def: "Inflammatory or noninflammatory diseases affecting the glomeruli of the nephron." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Cheilitis
data.def: "Inflammation of the lip." [HPO:sdoelken]
data.comment: It is associated with many conditions, including megaloblastic anemia from vitamin B12 deficiency, iron deficiency anemia (which in severe cases can lead to Plummer-Vinson syndrome) and oral candidiasis. It can also be a symptom of allergies, such as allergy to Balsam of Peru. Cheilitis can also be caused by taking the (retinoid) drug Isotretinoin. It may also be a pre-malignant lesion for squamous cell carcinoma.

data.name: Round ear
data.def: "Spontaneous flow of milk from the breast, unassociated with childbirth or nursing." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Benign neoplasm of the central nervous system
Malignant neoplasm of the central nervous system
data.def: "A tumor that originates in the pineal gland, has moderate cellularity and tends to form rosette patterns." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormal emotion/affect behavior
data.def: "An abnormality of emotional behaviour." [HPO:sdoelken]
data.comment: There are recurrent and painful eruptions of pustules on the palms and the soles of feet that may resolve with redbrown discoloration.

data.name: Abnormal fear/anxiety-related behavior
data.def: "An abnormality of fear/anxiety-related behavior, which may relate to either abnormally reduced fear/anxiety-related response or increased fear/anxiety-related response." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Aplasia of the musculature
data.def: "Absence of the musculature." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Duodenal stenosis
data.def: "The narrowing or partial blockage of a portion of the duodenum." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Abnormality of the palm
data.def: "An abnormality of the palm, that is, of the front of the hand." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of the plantar skin of foot
data.def: "An abnormality of the plantar part of foot, that is of the soles of the feet." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormality of the renal medulla
data.def: "An abnormality of the medulla of the kidney." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: The renal medulla is composed mainly of renal tubules.

data.name: Slanting of the palpebral fissure
data.def: "The presence of an abnormal shape of the palpebral fissure." [HPO:probinson]
data.comment: Bone age is usually determined by using a radiograph of the left hand to compare with images in the Greulich-Pyle atlas and approximating the closest skeletal age. \nIf the skeletal ages of individuals bones are different, i.e., different bones have (clearly) different levels of maturation, then it is refered to as dysharmonic skeletal maturation.

data.name: Abnormal size of the palpebral fissures
data.def: "An abnormal size of the palpebral fissures for example unusually long or short palpebral fissures." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Neoplasm of fatty tissue
data.def: "A tumor (abnormal growth of tissue) of adipose tissue." [HPO:sdoelken]

data.name: Corneal erosion
data.def: "An erosion or abrasion of the cornea's outermost layer of epithelial cells." [HPO:sdoelken]
data.comment: Note that protanomaly and deuteranomaly are both associated with difficulties distinguishing red and green.

data.name: Skin nodule
data.def: "Morphologically similar to a papule, but greater than either 10mm in both width and depth, and most frequently centered in the dermis or subcutaneous fat." [HPO:skoehler]
data.comment: The depth of involvement is what differentiates a nodule from a papule.

data.name: Pustule
data.def: "A small elevation of the skin containing cloudy or purulent material usually consisting of necrotic inflammatory cells." [HPO:skoehler]

data.name: Epidermoid cyst
data.def: "The presence of one or more cysts of the skin." [HPO:skoehler]
data.comment: A cyst is a cavity containing liquid, semisolid, or solid material. An epidermoid cyst is a benign cyst that develops out of ectodermal tissue and consists of a thin layer of squamous epithelium. An epidermoid cyst may or may not be painful or release pus, and are usually noticed as a bump on the skin.

data.name: Skin ulcer
data.def: "A discontinuity of the skin exhibiting complete loss of the epidermis and often portions of the dermis and even subcutaneous fat." [HPO:skoehler]

data.name: Verrucae
data.def: "Warts, benign growths on the skin or mucous membranes that cause cosmetic problems as well as pain and discomfort. Warts most often occur on the hands, feet, and genital areas." [HPO:skoehler]
data.comment: Cause is a virus called HPV (human papilloma virus), which infects the skin and causes the abnormal growth. There are many different varieties of the virus, which usually depends on the location of the lesion.

data.name: Absent/shortened dynein arms
data.def: "Absence of nail of little finger." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Epileptic encephalopathy
data.def: "Abnormal narrowing of the orifice of the mitral valve because of calcification of the mitral valve leaflets." [HPO:probinson]

data.name: Abnormal heart morphology
data.def: "Any structural anomaly of a heart." [GOC:TermGenie]
